text: Iredell County is a county of the U.S. state of North Carolina. At the 2020 census, the population was 186,693. Its county seat is Statesville, and its largest town is Mooresville. The county was formed in 1788.Martin, Jonathan; ==References== Category:18th-century establishments in North Carolina Category:1788 establishments in the United States Category:North Carolina counties
